<h2 class="h2">Clinical Care + Services</h2>
<section class="module structuredContent">
<p>We offer a wide range of services to prevent, diagnose and treat cancer. Our preventative
                        services include state-of-the-art genetic testing and risk-assessment counseling to help you
                        stay cancer-free throughout your lifetime. To help us diagnose cancer in its earliest —
                        and its most treatable—stages, we've invested in the latest technology, including 3-D
                        mammography for superior breast cancer screening. After diagnosis, our specialists can work with
                        you to find the best possible treatment plan for your cancer type, health history and lifestyle.
                        Wherever you are on your journey to beat cancer, we'll be by your side every step of the
                        way.</p>
</section>

<div class="content">
<h2 class="h2" id="calloutTitle-db66b7c1-4fc6-4421-8b23-8751302e1627">"They saved my life"</h2>
<p>
                            Joseph Laureanno, a patient of the Peritoneal Surface Malignancy Program, is grateful for
                            the quick thinking of our exceptional surgeons and the innovative HIPEC treatment that he
                            received.
                        </p>
<a aria-describedby="calloutTitle-db66b7c1-4fc6-4421-8b23-8751302e1627" class="mediaLink more" href="/News-Events-Media/News/Good-Medicine/2012/HIPEC-and-appendiceal-cancer-one-patients-story" id="right_rail_1_lnkMoreInfo">Read
                            his story now</a>
</div>

<section class="module structuredContent">
<p>There are many different types of health insurance and each insurance company may offer multiple
                        different plans to hundreds of employers and their employees.  For this reason, it is very
                        important that you understand the unique components of your plan and ask your health plan or
                        employer what care and services they will cover and what they expect you to pay for directly.
                        The best way to reach your insurer is typically the member services number on your insurance
                        card.</p>
<p>Below, we’ve listed the health insurance plans and products that are accepted at Tufts
                        Medical Center. If your health insurance company or plan is not listed, please contact your
                        health insurance provider to better understand your benefit plan and provider network available
                        to you.</p>
<p>Many insurance plans have different levels of costs for their members depending on where they
                        receive care. The information below can be used as a reference but you should check with your
                        plan to see what level of coverage you will receive for any care provided by Tufts Medical
                        Center. It is also important to check with your insurance plan to see if you need additional
                        referrals and/or authorizations before getting care at Tufts MC.</p>
<p>Emergency department physicians may not be in-network with all the payors or plans listed below.
                        Please contact your insurance company regarding coverage for the physician component of
                        emergency services at Tufts Medical Center.</p>
<h2>Co-payments</h2>
<p style="margin-bottom: 10pt;"><em>Please Note: <strong>Starting November 1, 2018, we can no longer
                        accept cash as a form of payment for deductibles, co-payments or co-insurance at Tufts Medical
                        Center and Tufts Children's Hospital outpatient clinics. </strong>We accept all forms of credit
                        cards, debit cards and personal checks. This change allows us to ensure proper documentation of
                        your payment. We apologize for any inconvenience and thank you for your
                        understanding. </em></p>
<p><em>This new policy applies to outpatient clinics only at Tufts MC. The pharmacy, Emergency
                        Department and the dining options within Tufts MC will still accept cash. <a href="/patient-care-services/Billing-and-Insurance/Cashless-copay">Learn more
                            &gt;</a></em></p>
<h2>Insurance payers and plans</h2>
<p>The level of coverage you receive is determined by your health insurance provider. Some
                        health insurance companies may use other companies to cover certain services such as mental
                        health or transplant-related services.  Some services may not be covered by your insurance
                        plan. Again, it is very important that you ask your health insurance provider or employer
                        what care and services they will cover and what they expect you to pay for directly. </p>
